    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>End-blown fipple flutes of the Andes, made of cane, bone, or wood, with a regionally varying number of fingerholes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
